# SubTrak UI Rules

## Component Library
- Use shadcn/ui components first: Dialog, Card, Form, Input, Button, Table, Badge, Select, Sheet, Toast, DropdownMenu, Skeleton
- Custom components only when shadcn has no equivalent
- Keep the dark glassmorphism theme: `bg-white/5`, `border-white/10`, `backdrop-blur`

## Every Screen Must Include
- Loading state (skeleton or spinner)
- Empty state (icon + message + CTA)
- Error state (alert with retry option)
- Success feedback (toast or inline message)

## Forms
- React Hook Form + Zod for all forms
- Reusable form field components where practical
- Inline validation messages
- Disable submit button during pending requests
- Consistent field styling via shadcn Form components

## Dashboard UX
- Metrics readable at a glance (MetricCard components)
- Subscription list supports search and filter
- Clicking a subscription opens a Dialog/modal
- Add/edit/delete interactions feel immediate (optimistic UI or fast refetch)

## Responsive Design
- Mobile-first approach
- Test all layouts at 375px, 768px, and 1280px breakpoints
- Navigation collapses to hamburger menu on mobile (already implemented)

## Accessibility
- All interactive elements must be keyboard-accessible
- Use semantic HTML elements
- Include aria-labels on icon-only buttons
